The Bloomberg Scarce Resources index tracks companies worldwide that are major players in one of the following sectors: oil & gas, aerospace & defence, agriculture, renewable energy and metals & mining. The ETF's TER (total expense ratio) amounts to 0.65% p.a.. The ETF replicates the performance of the underlying index by full replication (buying all the index constituents). The dividends in the ETF are accumulated and reinvested in the ETF. The First Trust Bloomberg Scarce Resources UCITS ETF Class A Accumulation is a very small ETF with 1m Euro assets under management. The ETF was launched on 23 January 2024 and is domiciled in Ireland.

name: Invesco BulletShares 2029 USD Corporate Bond UCITS ETF GBP Hdg Dist
description_en: The Invesco BulletShares 2029 USD Corporate Bond UCITS ETF GBP Hdg Dist seeks to track the Bloomberg 2029 Maturity USD Corporate Bond Screened (GBP Hedged) index. The Bloomberg 2029 Maturity USD Corporate Bond Screened (GBP Hedged) index tracks US dollar denominated corporate bonds. The index does not reflect a constant maturity range (as is the case with most other bond indices). Instead, only bonds that mature during the designated year (here: 2029) are included in the index. The index consists of ESG (environmental, social and governance) screened corporate bonds. Rating: Investment Grade. Maturity: December 2029 (the ETF will be closed afterwards). Currency hedged to British Pound (GBP). The ETF's TER (total expense ratio) amounts to 0.12% p.a.. The ETF replicates the performance of the underlying index by sampling technique (buying a selection of the most relevant index constituents). The interest income (coupons) in the ETF is distributed to the investors (Quarterly). The Invesco BulletShares 2029 USD Corporate Bond UCITS ETF GBP Hdg Dist is a very small ETF with 1m Euro assets under management. The ETF was launched on 2 July 2024 and is domiciled in Ireland.

description_en: The First Trust FactorFX UCITS ETF Acc is an actively managed ETF. The First Trust FactorFX Strategy is an actively managed investment strategy.
